[30.04.2026] — Inline-edit rolled to `/meetings` with the new `<InlineDateTimeCell>` primitive (§3.8) — sixth+seventh foundation primitives (datetime + nothing else new this round). Fields wired: `startsAt`, `type`, `location`. `status` deliberately skipped — transitions go through dedicated `markHappened` + `cancelMeeting` actions that capture outcome/reason metadata, naive inline status would skip those. Per-row `canEdit` flag threaded from the page (computed via the now-shared `lib/meetings/permissions.ts` → `canEditMeeting()`, promoted from a private helper inside `[id]/actions.ts`); disables cells for non-assignees + cancelled meetings; server actions enforce same rule independently. Timezone handling exposed publicly: `sofiaWallClockToUtc` (already existed) + new `utcToSofiaWallClock` in `lib/meetings/parse.ts` — the cell speaks Sofia wall-clock strings, server converts at the seam. New audit action `meetings.field.updated` with `{ field, before, after }` payload, mirrors contacts/tasks pattern.

[30.04.2026] — Copy reconciliation pass landed alongside `bg-copy.md`: (1) `Опитай отново` → `Повтори` in `file-preview-modal.tsx` (line 392); also updated the two foundation specs (`ui-patterns-files.md`, `ui-patterns-inline-edit.md`) where the older string was quoted. (2) `Няма задачи в този изглед.` → `Няма намерени задачи.` in `app/(app)/tasks/{page,tasks-table}.tsx`. (3) `Без отговорник` → `— Без отговорник` in 4 places (contacts detail, tasks detail inline-cells, tasks-table, leads-table). The 5th hit in `app/(app)/leads/[id]/page.tsx` (warning StatusBadge for unassigned leads) kept as `Без отговорник` per a new spec exception in §6: the em-dash reads as noise inside a colored chip. Drift list in §15 cleared; section retained for future entries. Typecheck/lint/build all green.

[30.04.2026] — `specs/_foundations/bg-copy.md` shipped as first draft — canonical Bulgarian strings for buttons, confirmations, empty states, "no value" placeholders, validation errors, toasts, plurals (count form), locked-field tooltips, system attribution, address forms (formal "Вие" except destructive-confirm prompts). Surfaces three real drift items found by a 2-minute grep audit: (1) `Опитай отново` (file modal) vs `Повтори` (inline cells) — pick `Повтори`; (2) `Няма задачи в този изглед.` vs `Няма намерени X.` — unify to the latter; (3) `Без отговорник` vs `— Без отговорник` placeholder inconsistency. None blocking — listed in §15 for follow-up "copy reconciliation" PR. Spec is a writing guide + dictionary, not translation infrastructure; product is Bulgarian-only by design.

[30.04.2026] — Inline-edit treatment rolled to `/leads` (source) and `/tasks` (title + due-date). New server actions: `setLeadSource` (rejects email-sourced values per LEAD_SOURCE_USER_SELECTABLE; `email_form` / `email_unparsed` stay system-only set by the Resend webhook), `setTaskTitle` (required, max 200), `setTaskDueDate`. New audit actions: `leads.source.changed`, `tasks.field.updated` (granular field updates from inline cells). Promoted the previously-inlined `<ReadOnlyBadge>` to `components/ui/read-only-badge.tsx` so contacts/leads/tasks share one source. Spec wiring lists in §3.1 (status), §3.4 (text), §3.7 (date), §3.12 (read-only) updated. Properties + most of contracts deferred — properties needs its older one-off `<InlineCell>` migrated to the foundation primitives (separate refactor); contracts fields are mostly contract-locked per spec §9.

[30.04.2026] — Inline-edit foundation expanded with 4 new primitives — `<InlineTextCell>`, `<InlineMultilineCell>`, `<InlineDateCell>`, `<InlineRelationCell>` — bringing the foundation to 6 of the 12 spec field types built (status, person, text, multiline, date, relation). Wired into the `/contacts` table to make every field on the Contact model inline-editable: name, type, phone, email, ЕГН, address, properties, notes, birthDate, building, owner. Read-only fields (createdAt, age, birthdayThisYear) get a 🔒 hover badge per spec §3.12. New `contact.field.updated` audit action with `{ field, before, after }` payload (one entry per field change — keeps the audit log granular without bloating the AuditAction union with one action per field). Per-field server actions (`setContactName`, `setContactPhone`, ..., 9 total in `field-actions.ts`) — server-side validation (email regex, ЕГН via `lib/bg-id.ts`, length caps, building must be active). Validation behavior: invalid input rolls back with a Bulgarian toast; ЕГН checksum failure is non-blocking (per `specs/contacts.md` §6) but format/length errors reject. Date wire format is ISO YYYY-MM-DD; display uses `formatDate` (DD.MM.YYYY).

[30.04.2026] — Tasks module shipped end-to-end as a standalone module per `specs/tasks.md` (greenfield — spec written + code shipped together). `Task` Prisma model + `TaskStatus` enum (todo/in_progress/done). Three-tab list page (Мои / Всички / Завършени) with badge counts. Detail page + create + edit forms. Inline status + owner cells via the foundation primitives — proves the third independent consumer of `<InlineStatusCell>` and the third of `<InlinePersonCell>`. Permissions: open team-wide for create/edit/status/assign per user direction; admin-only delete. Setting status → done auto-stamps `completedAt`; moving back clears it. Overdue indication via left border on title cell when `dueDate < today` and status ≠ done. Deliberate non-features (out of v1, listed in spec §2): entity links, multi-assignee, priority, recurrence, email reminders, file attachments, activity feed. Each is a small additive change when demand appears.

[30.04.2026] — Admin delete UI for contracts attachments wired into the file preview modal. Two-step confirm pattern (Click 🗑 → toolbar swaps to a danger-tone confirm row with [Изтрий завинаги] [Отказ] buttons; auto-resets after 5s). The `<FilePreviewModal>` and `<FileCell>` got an optional `onDelete` prop — when undefined, no delete affordance renders. Per spec §8.1 deletion is admin-only, so `canDeleteAttachments = me.role === "admin"` is computed once in the page and threaded to the cell. Both the `/contracts` table and the `/contracts/[id]` Files section get the same delete capability via the shared `<ContractFiles>` wrapper. Rebuild confirmed: typecheck/lint/build all green.

[30.04.2026] — `<InlineStatusCell>` primitive shipped (`components/ui/inline-status-cell.tsx`), generic over the enum value type with optional `systemOnly` flag for picker-hidden values (e.g. Lead.status `converted` is set by the Contracts conversion flow, not user-pickable). Wired into `/leads` (all roles can edit) and `/contracts` (admin/manager only — the cell is `disabled` for users via a `canEditStatus` flag threaded from the page; the action also requires the role server-side). New actions `setLeadStatus`, `setContractStatus`, `setPropertyStatus`. Visual: each option in the popover renders with the same `<StatusBadge>` tone classes as the trigger so the popover reads as "buttons that *are* the badge". Search input only renders when there are >4 options (contracts has 3 → no search; properties will have 8 → search). Properties table NOT migrated this round — it has an older one-off `<InlineCell>` predating the foundation that handles status + type + seller; migration is a separate refactor. The `setPropertyStatus` action is staged for that migration. The `+ Нов статус` admin-inline-create button (spec §3.1) is deferred — adding values to a string enum is schema work.

[30.04.2026] — `applyCarryover` extended with a backward pass (`computeCarryover` exposes both the per-payment view + final unused credit). Forward pass alone left the per-payment "Остава" view summing to a different number than the contract-level total when an overpayment landed on a milestone whose subsequent dues were all 0 — the unused credit just sat in the chain, never consumed. Backward pass walks the per-payment list oldest-first and consumes any final leftover credit against earlier `adjustedRemainingEur` values, so sum-of-payments now matches the contract net. Detail page shows "Покрито от бъдещо надплащане" badge per payment when this kicked in, plus a "Свободен кредит" footer when the contract is net-overpaid (rare but real — e.g. fee refunds).

[30.04.2026] — Inline owner edit ported to `/leads` (`InlinePersonCell` + `setLeadOwner` server action). Mirror of the contacts pattern; same permission model (any signed-in profile can reassign). The `leads.owner.changed` audit action already existed from the original leads ship — just a new emission point. Confirms the primitive's reusability claim; same-shape callsite, different module.

[30.04.2026] — Contracts attachments wired up end-to-end (first production consumer of the file-cell pattern). Added `ContractAttachment` Prisma model, extended `lib/supabase/storage.ts` with `uploadFile` / `deleteFile` / `ensureBucketExists` (auto-creates the `contracts` bucket private, 25 MB cap on first call). Server actions `uploadContractAttachment` / `deleteContractAttachment` (delete is admin-only per spec §9). `<FileCell>` got a "+" upload button trailing the icon stack. Detail page `/contracts/[id]` now has a "Файлове" section rendering the same `<FileCell>` — table and detail share the data via revalidatePath, so uploads propagate automatically. Demo wiring (`lib/files/demo.ts`, `contracts.demo` switch case, `/public/demo/*`) deleted. Foundation spec §2 updated: upload UX is now in scope for the table cell (modules opt out via not passing `onUpload`).

[30.04.2026] — Cross-module file-attachment pattern shipped as a foundation (`specs/_foundations/ui-patterns-files.md`): `<FileCell>` icon stack inline, `<FilePreviewModal>` modal viewer, `POST /api/files/sign` as the single signing endpoint with per-module dispatch. First Supabase Storage usage (`lib/supabase/storage.ts`) — service-role client, 5-min signed URLs, silent re-fetch 30s before expiry. Modal renders PDFs via native `<iframe>` (no PDF.js dep) and images via `<img>`; non-previewable types fall back to a download CTA. Demo wiring in `lib/files/demo.ts` + `module: "contracts.demo"` switch case is throwaway — remove when contracts attachments ship. Why a generic primitive: contracts and invoices both already design `*Attachment` tables in their specs, and shipping a one-off cell per module would diverge.

[30.04.2026] — First inline-edit cell shipped: owner column on `/contacts` (see `components/ui/inline-person-cell.tsx`, `app/(app)/contacts/owner-actions.ts`). Built as a reusable primitive — leads/tasks/etc. will share it. Implements the canonical pattern from `_foundations/ui-patterns-inline-edit.md` §3.9 (popover, search-as-you-type, ↑/↓ + Enter, "— Без отговорник" first, full optimistic with rollback). Also added: minimal `<ToastProvider>` (no library — kept dep-free per CLAUDE.md), `<AvatarCircle>` initials primitive (deterministic palette over existing tokens), `contact.owner.changed` audit action. Permissions: matches spec — any signed-in profile can reassign (no role gate beyond `requireProfile`). Popover uses `position: fixed` with computed coords because the Table wrapper has `overflow-hidden`. Inactive owners stay rendered as the current value with a `(неактивен)` tag but never appear in the picker list.

[27.04.2026] — Admin calendar edit form replaces the old "Работен ден" checkbox + free-text name with a 3-option select (`holiday` / `working` / `compensatory`); the checkbox + name combo silently allowed `isWorking=true, holidayName="X"` ghost rows that didn't render anywhere (caught when 6 May 2026 / Гергьовден was marked but invisible). The select makes intent unambiguous; `isAnnotatedOnly` paint (warning-50 ring) on the grid surfaces any pre-existing ghost rows so admins can re-edit them. Also fixed `yearStart`/`yearEnd` bounds: were noon UTC, missed Jan 1 overrides stored at midnight (see `app/(app)/admin/calendar/{page,actions}.tsx`).

[24.04.2026] — Spec folder restructured: `docs/` → `specs/` with `_foundations/`, `design-system/`, top-level lowercase module files — matches `CLAUDE.md` + `_index.md`; every cross-reference now resolves.

[24.04.2026] — LP2-C (Resend inbound webhook) wired up. Resend's `email.received` payload is metadata-only; raw MIME must be fetched via `GET /emails/receiving/{email_id}` using `data.email_id` from the webhook, then the signed `raw.download_url` from that response (see `app/api/leads/ingest/route.ts`'s `fetchResendRawMime`). Required a **full-access** API key; a restricted/sending-only key returns empty lists on `/emails/receiving` (silent — no 401/403). Store the key in `RESEND_API_KEY` — same var used for outbound.

[23.04.2026] — `Property.owner` unlocked for manual editing in Phase 1 until Contracts ships — otherwise there's no way to express ownership at all; re-locks automatically once a `contractId` is set (see `lib/properties/permissions.ts`).

[23.04.2026] — Contact typeahead search excludes the `notes` column — notes carry relationship/alias text that surfaced contacts for non-obvious reasons when searching for owners (see `lib/contacts/search.ts`).

[23.04.2026] — Contact typeahead result limit is 25 (up from 10), with a "Показани първите 25" footer when the list is maxed out so users know more matches may exist.

[22.04.2026] — Properties CSV seed is Windows-1251, not UTF-8 — verified by reading raw bytes (`D1 E3 F0 E0 E4 E0` = `Сграда` in CP-1251). The import script uses `TextDecoder("windows-1251")`; reading as UTF-8 produces mojibake and collapses many buildings into the same string (see `scripts/import-properties.ts`, `specs/properties.md` §7.1).

[22.04.2026] — `landPct` / `yardPct` column precision is `decimal(10, 6)` not `(8, 6)` — one CSV row has `landPct = 203` (data error); bumping precision lets the import complete rather than reject a single outlier (see `prisma/schema.prisma`).

[22.04.2026] — The 2,158-row CSV has 311 duplicate `(Сграда, Name)` pairs → only 1,847 unique properties after import. `(buildingId, name)` is the natural key; second occurrence wins (see `specs/properties.md` §7.3).
