# Renovations

Project module for post-handover renovation work on units the company has already sold + delivered, with future-ready scope for pre-handover unit-prep work the company does on its own inventory. Phase 2 — depends on Properties (1) and Contacts (2). Not part of Phase 1.

Out of scope for Phase 2 (called out explicitly in §13): client billing, money/budget tracking, common-area building work, predecessor task links / proper PERT scheduling. The first two move in a follow-up phase once the operational shape stabilises; the latter two are deferred unless usage demands them.

Cross-cutting foundations referenced throughout: `_foundations/ui-patterns-inline-edit.md`, `_foundations/ui-patterns-relations.md`, `_foundations/roles.md`, `_foundations/audit-log.md` (pending), `design-system/tokens.md`, `design-system/tables.md` (pending), `design-system/modals.md`.

## 1. Purpose
After the company hands a unit over to a buyer, the buyer occasionally asks the company back to do renovation work (small repairs, partial refits, full refurbs). This module is the operational home of those projects: who, where, what scope, what timeline, what's the status, which company employee owns the execution.

A project is **one renovation = one property**. Property → Renovations is 1:many (cardinality already declared in `_foundations/ui-patterns-relations.md` §4). A single property can accumulate multiple renovation records over its lifetime; each renovation stands on its own.

Phase 2 scope is operational, not financial — see §13 for the deliberate exclusions.

## 2. Two creation paths (now + future)

**Phase 2 ships path A. Path B is a schema-ready future addition — the model accommodates it from day one so we don't migrate later.**

| Path | Trigger | `requestedByContactId` | Typical status start |
|---|---|---|---|
| A. Owner-requested (Phase 2 primary) | A previous buyer calls in asking for work on their unit. | The buying contact (Property.owner). | `draft` → operator drafts a scope → `quoted` |
| B. Pre-handover unit prep (future) | Internal decision by the company to refresh an inventory unit before listing or handover. | `null` — no external client. | `approved` → straight into execution (no quote step) |

The model supports both because `Renovation.requestedByContactId` is nullable from the start. UI affordances for path B (e.g. a "Вътрешен ремонт" toggle on the create form) will be added in Phase 2.5 when the workflow firms up; the spec mentions them so the schema does not need a migration.

**Explicitly not modelled** (see §13): resale refurbishment of returned units, common-area / building-level work. Both could be retrofitted onto this module but each has its own quirks — defer until the company actually does enough of them to justify the UX.

## 3. Data model

### 3.1 `Renovation`
| Field | BG label | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | — | UUID PK | — |
| `propertyId` | Имот | FK → Property | Required, the unit the project applies to. Hard-block deletion of the parent property while at least one renovation exists (already declared in `properties.md` §5.3). |
| `title` | Заглавие | string, ≤200 chars | Required. Free text. Default suggestion on create: `Ремонт — <property.name>`. |
| `type` | Тип | string | Free-text categorisation tag (per §3.3). Will be promoted to an enum once the team settles on the canonical 5 names. |
| `status` | Статус | enum (§3.2) | Required. Defaults to `draft`. |
| `description` | Описание | string?, ≤4000 | Long-form scope description. Markdown not parsed in Phase 2 — plain text only. |
| `requestedByContactId` | Заявител | FK → Contact, nullable | The buyer who asked. `null` for internal pre-handover prep (path B). |
| `managerId` | Отговорник | FK → Profile, nullable | Company employee responsible for execution. Defaults to the creator on insert; assignable to any active profile thereafter. |
| `plannedStartDate` | Планирано начало | date?, optional | Used as the anchor for the per-renovation Gantt (§6). |
| `plannedEndDate` | Планиран край | date?, optional | — |
| `actualStartDate` | Реално начало | date?, optional | Stamped automatically when `status` transitions into `in_progress` if blank; editable thereafter. |
| `actualEndDate` | Реално завършване | date?, optional | Stamped automatically when `status` transitions into `done` if blank; editable thereafter. |
| `createdAt` | Създаден | timestamp | System. |
| `updatedAt` | Последна промяна | timestamp | System. |
| `createdById` | — | FK → Profile | System. Captured at insert. |
| `deletedAt` | — | timestamp?, soft-delete | System. Same soft-delete pattern as Properties + Contacts. |

### 3.2 Statuses
The user-locked lifecycle (6 states) — supports a quote-then-approve gate upfront even though Phase 2 doesn't track money.

| Value | Bulgarian label | Tone | Meaning |
|---|---|---|---|
| `draft` | Чернова | `neutral` | Operator is still defining the scope; not communicated to the client yet. |
| `quoted` | Оферта | `info` | Scope + indicative timing communicated to the client (verbally or offline). Awaiting acceptance. |
| `approved` | Одобрена | `accent` | Client accepted; work hasn't started yet. Path B (pre-handover) enters here. |
| `in_progress` | В процес | `warning` | Work has started. Triggers auto-stamp of `actualStartDate` if blank. |
| `done` | Завършена | `success` | Work complete. Triggers auto-stamp of `actualEndDate` if blank. |
| `cancelled` | Отказана | `neutral-outline` | Project killed at any point. Captured as a terminal state distinct from `done` for reporting. |

Transitions are open: any state can move to any other (no enforced workflow gates). The reason: real renovation jobs go back and forth (`in_progress` → `on hold` → back to `quoted` for re-scope). Hard-coding a state machine would create more friction than guidance. The status history (§5) is the audit trail of every transition; managers eyeball it for unusual patterns.

`on_hold` is **not** in the canonical list — the team voted for 6 states. If a project pauses, the manager moves it back to `approved` (or `quoted` if scope is being rediscussed). This trade-off is deliberate; revisit if managers actually ask for the state.

### 3.3 Type tag
Free text in Phase 2 (`string`, nullable). The "5 templates" wording from `_foundations/context.md` describes a categorisation layer the team will eventually formalise; per the locked decision this round, picking a type does **not** auto-seed tasks or copy a project template — it's just a label used for filtering + reporting.

Once the 5 canonical names are settled, the field becomes an enum + the spec lists them with tones. Until then, the create form offers a small Bulgarian datalist (`<input list>`) of distinct existing values to nudge naming consistency, same approach as `Property.sellers`.

### 3.4 `RenovationTask`
**Deliberate decision (this round):** renovation tasks are a **separate model** from the standalone `Task` module. No shared schema, no shared UI, no cross-surfacing in `/tasks → Мои`. The two domains describe different work — standalone tasks are personal/team todos with no entity links by design (`tasks.md` §1); renovation tasks are project sub-items tied 1:many to a parent `Renovation`. Keeping them apart avoids polluting the standalone module with project-aware filters + lets each side evolve at its own pace.

| Field | BG label | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | — | UUID PK | — |
| `renovationId` | — | FK → Renovation | Required. Cascade on parent soft-delete. |
| `title` | Заглавие | string, ≤200 | Required. |
| `description` | Описание | string?, ≤2000 | Optional. |
| `assigneeId` | Изпълнител | FK → Profile, nullable | The employee actually doing this task. Defaults to the parent renovation's `managerId` on insert. |
| `startDate` | Начало | date?, optional | Independent of other tasks (no predecessor links per the locked decision). |
| `endDate` | Край | date?, optional | — |
| `status` | Статус | enum (§3.5) | Required. Defaults to `planned`. |
| `sortOrder` | — | int | For stable ordering inside the renovation. Default = `now()` epoch on insert; reorderable in a Phase 2.5 drag handle. |
| `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `createdById` | — | system | — |

### 3.5 Task statuses
A 4-state set deliberately simpler than the parent renovation. Renovation lifecycle is about project + client communication; tasks are about execution.

| Value | Bulgarian label | Tone |
|---|---|---|
| `planned` | Планирана | `info` |
| `in_progress` | В процес | `warning` |
| `done` | Завършена | `success` |
| `cancelled` | Отказана | `neutral-outline` |

No "blocked" status — if a task is blocked, the manager either moves it to `cancelled` (replace with a different task) or leaves it as `in_progress` with a note. Same pragmatic stance as the renovation lifecycle.

## 4. Routes

| Route | Purpose | Roles |
|---|---|---|
| `/renovations` | List view + portfolio Gantt toggle (§5) | All signed-in |
| `/renovations/new` | Create a renovation (modal or page; see §5.2) | All signed-in |
| `/renovations/[id]` | Detail page: per-task list + per-task Gantt (§6) | All signed-in; edit gated per §7 |
| `/renovations/[id]/edit` | Full-form edit of the parent renovation | Admin / Manager / assigned manager |

Task create/edit happens inline on the detail page — no separate routes per task (matches how `/contracts/[id]` handles its payments + installments).

## 5. List + portfolio views

### 5.1 Default list (table view)
Standard Airtable-style table, same chrome as `/properties` and `/contacts`. Default columns:

1. Заглавие (links to detail)
2. Имот (building displayName + unit name, `<InlineRelationCell>`-style read-only display + click-through)
3. Тип
4. Статус — `<InlineStatusCell>` with the 6 tones
5. Отговорник — `<InlinePersonCell>`, active profiles only
6. Планирано начало → Планиран край (combined cell: `02.06.2026 → 18.07.2026`)
7. Прогрес — small progress bar showing % of tasks in `done`. Tooltip lists the breakdown.
8. Създаден (read-only with 🔒 per `_foundations/ui-patterns-inline-edit.md` §3.12)

Hidden-by-default: Заявител, Реално начало, Реално завършване, Описание (truncated).

**Filters** (top of table, collapsible, same pattern as other lists):
- Статус (multi-select)
- Тип (multi-select)
- Отговорник (multi-select with "Без отговорник" option)
- Сграда — parses through `property.buildingId`
- Заявител — contact picker, single-select
- Период — date-range over `plannedStartDate`. Useful for "what's scheduled this quarter."
- "Само просрочени" toggle — projects whose `plannedEndDate < today` and `status ∉ {done, cancelled}`

**Search**: ILIKE across `title` + `description` + the linked property's `name` + the linked contact's `fullName`. Same Bulgarian-aware behavior as Contacts search.

**Pagination**: 50 per page (renovations are heavier visually than contacts; smaller page reads better). URL-driven, same shape as the other lists.

### 5.2 Create flow
Modal-on-list, not a separate page — renovation creation usually happens while the operator is already looking at the renovations list or at a specific property. Two entry points:

1. **From `/renovations` → `+ Нов ремонт`** — opens the create modal. Property + buyer picker fields blank.
2. **From `/properties/[id]` → "Ремонти" relations panel → `+ Нов ремонт`** — opens the same modal with `propertyId` + `requestedByContactId` pre-filled from the property's `owner`.

Required: `propertyId`, `title`. Everything else optional including `type` (you may not know the category at the draft stage). `status` defaults to `draft`. `managerId` defaults to the creator.

After create the user lands on the detail page with the task list empty + the inline "+ Добави задача" affordance focused.

### 5.3 Portfolio Gantt view
Toggleable from `/renovations` — a tab control above the table flips the table out for a Gantt strip. Each row is one renovation; each bar runs from `plannedStartDate` to `plannedEndDate`. Bars are tinted by status (using the same tones as the status cell), so a viewer scans color first.

Phase 2 ships a **read-only** portfolio Gantt — drag-to-reschedule is a Phase 2.5 enhancement. The filter bar still applies (same chips), so a manager can scope to "В процес" + "Сграда: Сердика" and see only those projects on the timeline.

Today's date renders as a vertical accent-tone line across the Gantt.

### 5.4 Header KPIs
A 4-tile strip above the list/Gantt, same pattern as `/invoices`:

1. **Активни проекти** — count of renovations in `quoted` / `approved` / `in_progress`.
2. **В процес сега** — count in `in_progress`. Subtitle: total open tasks in those projects.
3. **Просрочени** — count of renovations with `plannedEndDate < today` and not yet `done`/`cancelled`. Danger tone when non-zero.
4. **Завършени тримесечие** — count moved to `done` in the current calendar quarter.

KPIs respect the active filters (same decision the invoices module made last round in `decisions.md` 12.05.2026).

## 6. Detail page

`/renovations/[id]` is the operational home for a single project. Layout matches the contracts detail-page pattern: a header block, a relations strip, a tabbed body.

### 6.1 Header block
- Title (`<InlineTextCell>`, required, max 200)
- Status badge (`<InlineStatusCell>`)
- Type tag (`<InlineTextCell>` with `suggestions` from distinct existing values)
- Three pills: property (link), buyer (link or "—"), responsible manager (avatar + name)
- Edit button (links to `/renovations/[id]/edit` for full-form edits)
- Delete button (admin only)

### 6.2 Dates panel
Two columns of date inline cells:
- Планирано начало / Планиран край (`<InlineDateCell>`)
- Реално начало / Реално завършване (`<InlineDateCell>`, auto-stamped on status transitions to `in_progress` / `done` when blank — see §3.1)

The two "actual" cells show the 🔒 tooltip when blank with a hint that they auto-fill on status change (`Попълва се автоматично при преминаване към „В процес"`). Editable thereafter.

### 6.3 Tasks tab (default)
Inline-editable task list. Columns:
- Заглавие — `<InlineTextCell>`
- Изпълнител — `<InlinePersonCell>`
- Начало → Край — two `<InlineDateCell>`s; renders as combined display when both set, `—` placeholder otherwise
- Статус — `<InlineStatusCell>` (4 task tones)
- Бележка / Описание — `<InlineMultilineCell>` (truncated preview)

Footer of the list has a `+ Добави задача` affordance — creates a placeholder row inline (title focus), saves on blur. Same UX shape as the line-items editor on invoices (`/invoices/[id]`).

Bulk actions intentionally **not** in Phase 2 — matches the parked decision from `decisions.md` on multi-select. Reintroduce if usage demands.

### 6.4 Gantt tab
Same data as the tasks tab, rendered as horizontal bars indexed by row (one bar per task) along a time axis. Read-only in Phase 2 (drag-to-reschedule deferred). Today's date renders as a vertical accent line. Tasks missing `startDate` or `endDate` are listed in a side panel labelled "Без дати" — they don't appear on the bar chart.

The time-axis range auto-fits to the union of all task date ranges, with a 7-day pad on each side. A "Покажи целия проект" toggle expands the range to the renovation's planned start/end.

### 6.5 Связани записи (sidebar)
Per `_foundations/ui-patterns-relations.md`: a small panel listing
- Имот → link + summary chip (building, unit, status badge)
- Заявител → contact summary chip
- Договор (if the property has one) → link with contract number

The reverse direction lives on those records' detail pages (Property → Ремонти tab; Contact → Ремонти tab) — already noted in `properties.md` §4 and `contacts.md` §6.

## 7. Permissions
Per `_foundations/roles.md` (full matrix lives there). Summary:

| Role | Create | Edit own renovations | Edit any renovation | Delete | View |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| admin | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ (soft) | all |
| manager | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ | all |
| user | ✅ | only those they're assigned as manager/assignee | ❌ | ❌ | all |

Open creation matches the stance of every other module — friction here doesn't help anyone. Edit-gating is per-record at the field level: users can change the status / assign tasks on renovations where they're the responsible manager or have a task assigned, but cannot rewrite the parent project's metadata (title, type, scope description, dates).

Delete is admin-only and soft (sets `deletedAt`). Hard delete is not exposed in Phase 2.

**Locked-field behavior** (per `_foundations/ui-patterns-inline-edit.md` §3.12): when a user lacks permission, the cell renders disabled with a `🔒` and a Bulgarian tooltip explaining why.

## 8. Audit log
Per `_foundations/audit-log.md` (pending) — every mutation logs:

- `renovation.created`
- `renovation.updated` (full-form edits via `/edit`)
- `renovation.field.updated` — granular per-field audit from inline cells. Payload: `{ field }`; `before` / `after` carry the per-field values. Same shape as `contact.field.updated`, `tasks.field.updated`, `property.updated`.
- `renovation.status_changed` — emitted in addition to `field.updated` when the status field changes, so reporting can filter on it directly.
- `renovation.deleted` — soft delete.
- `renovation.task.created`
- `renovation.task.updated`
- `renovation.task.status_changed`
- `renovation.task.deleted` — soft delete; tasks inherit the parent's deletion when the renovation is removed.

Audit entries include `before` / `after` for diffable fields and `payload` for non-diff context (e.g. `{ field: "title" }`).

## 9. Notifications
**Phase 2.5**, not Phase 2. The `_foundations/context.md` requirement mentions "notifications" but doesn't specify which. The candidates:

- Task `endDate < today` and not `done` → in-app indicator on the renovation row + top-nav badge for the assignee (mirrors the `/tasks` badge pattern).
- Renovation `plannedEndDate < today` and not `done` → row indicator + the КПИ tile counts it.
- Status transitions → email digest to the responsible manager (next-day batch).

None of these block Phase 2 shipping; the data model supports all of them when the time comes.

## 10. Top-nav badge
Same shape as `/tasks` and the absence inbox: the "Ремонти" header link carries an accent-tone badge with the count of `me's open renovations where (managerId = me.id) AND (status IN (quoted, approved, in_progress))`. Hidden when 0.

`me`'s assigned **tasks** don't roll up here in Phase 2 — that would compete with the existing tasks badge for the same eyeballs. Revisit in Phase 2.5 if managers want it.

## 11. Status history
Like Properties, every status change on a renovation writes a row to `RenovationStatusHistory(renovationId, fromStatus, toStatus, authorId, note?, createdAt)`. Rendered on the detail page as a chronological log under the relations sidebar.

**Why a dedicated history table** (vs. relying on the audit log): the audit log is the system-wide append-only event ledger and is queried per-actor / per-action, not per-record. The per-record status history is denormalised for fast list rendering on the detail page. Same pattern as `PropertyStatusHistory`.

`RenovationTask.status` changes do **not** get a dedicated history table in Phase 2 — too noisy. Audit log entries (`renovation.task.status_changed`) are enough for the rare retrospective.

## 12. Integration with other modules

| Module | Direction | What |
|---|---|---|
| Properties | inbound | A Property can have N Renovations. Detail page surfaces them in the relations panel; deletion is blocked while any exist. |
| Contacts | inbound | A Contact may be the `requestedByContact` of N Renovations. Detail page lists them under the existing "Ремонти" tab. |
| Tasks | none | Deliberate decision — renovation tasks are a separate model; the standalone `/tasks` module never surfaces them. |
| Invoices | future | The `renovation` invoice section is already seeded (`scripts/seed-invoice-sections.sql`). Phase 3 will link invoices to renovations for per-project cost tracking. The current `invoices.md` §15 already calls this out. |
| Audit log | outbound | Every mutation logs (§8). |

## 13. Out of scope (Phase 2)
Deliberate exclusions, documented so a future reader doesn't assume oversight:

- **Money / budget / actuals.** No `budgetEur`, no `actualEur`, no client invoicing flow. Renovations in Phase 2 are operationally tracked but financially silent. Cost tracking comes via the invoice-linking integration in Phase 3.
- **Predecessor task links.** Gantt is a visualisation of independent date ranges (§3.4). No `Task → Task` "depends on" edges, no cycle detection, no automatic shift on a parent change. Adds real complexity; deferred unless the team adopts MS-Project-style planning.
- **Template-driven auto-seeding.** Picking a type does not clone a stored task list (§3.3). The 5 templates from `context.md` will arrive in a Phase 2.5 cycle once the canonical names settle.
- **Drag-to-reschedule on the Gantt.** Read-only in Phase 2 (§5.3 + §6.4). Editing is via the inline-edit cells in the table.
- **Common-area / building work.** The schema requires `propertyId`. If the company starts doing lobby / facade / elevator projects regularly, we add a parallel `BuildingRenovation` model or generalise this one — defer until the demand is concrete.
- **Resale refurbishment of returned units.** Conceptually similar to path B (pre-handover prep), and the schema would accommodate it (`requestedByContactId = null`). Just not in the v1 UI — add when needed.
- **On-hold status.** Voted out of the lifecycle (§3.2). Reintroduce if managers actively miss it.
- **Bulk operations on renovations or tasks.** Same parking decision as the rest of the system per `decisions.md`.

## 14. Open questions to resolve before code
None blocking — the model is settled. The two follow-ups that will need real-world feedback to lock in:

1. **The 5 type names.** Need them from the team before we can promote `type` from string to enum (§3.3).
2. **Notification cadence.** Confirm whether email digests are wanted at all, or whether the in-app badge + row indicator is enough (§9).

Neither blocks the schema or the Phase 2 UI — both can be retrofitted without migrations.
</file>

<file path="specs/tasks.md">
# Tasks

## 1. Purpose

Lightweight personal + team to-do tracker. Sales calls to make, paperwork to file, "remember to email the bank" — anything the team wants written down and assigned. Standalone module — no links to Contacts / Leads / Contracts / Properties in v1, by design.

The team is 25 people. We don't need a Jira; we need a shared list everyone can see, assign, and check off.

## 2. Scope

In scope (v1):
- Title + optional description.
- Single owner (assignee). Optional — unassigned tasks are valid.
- Optional due date (DATE granularity, no time-of-day).
- Three statuses: `todo` / `in_progress` / `done`.
- Three tabs at `/tasks`: Мои / Всички / Завършени.
- Inline status + owner editing on the list, via the foundation primitives.
- Overdue indication when `dueDate < today` and status ≠ `done`.

Out of scope (v1, deliberately):
- Links to other entities (Contact / Lead / Contract / Property). The team can add the entity reference in the description if relevant.
- Multi-assignee / collaborators.
- Priority field.
- Subtasks / parent-child structure.
- Recurring tasks.
- Email reminders / digest.
- File attachments.
- Activity feed per task.

These are all easy to add when there's demand — keeping v1 tight.

## 3. Permissions

Open team-wide:
- **Create** — anyone (admin / manager / user).
- **Edit** (title, description, due date) — anyone.
- **Change status** — anyone, including marking another person's task done.
- **Reassign owner** — anyone.

Restricted:
- **Delete** — admin only. Destructive, no soft-delete in v1.

Rationale: the team is small, communication channels are tight. Friction from per-record ownership rules wouldn't pay back.

## 4. Data model

```
Task
  ├─ id
  ├─ title              (required, max 200 chars)
  ├─ description        (optional, free text, multiline)
  ├─ status             (todo | in_progress | done — Prisma enum)
  ├─ dueDate            (DATE, optional)
  ├─ ownerId            (FK → Profile, optional)
  ├─ createdById        (FK → Profile, optional)
  ├─ createdAt
  ├─ updatedAt
  └─ completedAt        (set when status → done; cleared when leaving done)
```

Indexes: `ownerId`, `status`, `dueDate`. Sorting: status asc → dueDate asc (nulls last) → createdAt desc.

Lives in `public` schema.

## 5. Pages

### 5.1 `/tasks` — list

Three tabs:
- **Мои** (default) — `ownerId = currentUser`, `status ∈ (todo, in_progress)`.
- **Всички** — any owner, `status ∈ (todo, in_progress)`.
- **Завършени** — any owner, `status = done`.

Each tab shows a count badge. Tab state lives in the URL (`?tab=mine|all|done`) so links and reloads preserve it.

Default columns: Заглавие · Статус · Отговорник · Краен срок. Hidden by default: Създадена · Завършена. Column visibility is persisted per-user via `useColumnVisibility` (key `tasks:visible-columns`).

Inline editing — all editable fields are click-to-edit from the table:
- **Заглавие** via `<InlineTextCell>` (required, max 200 chars). A small ↗ link icon sits next to the cell to open the detail page when the user wants the fuller view.
- **Статус** via `<InlineStatusCell>`.
- **Отговорник** via `<InlinePersonCell>`.
- **Краен срок** via `<InlineDateCell>` (native date picker).
- **Създадена** / **Завършена** — read-only with 🔒 badge.

Overdue rows: tasks with `dueDate < today` and `status ≠ done` get a `border-l-2 border-danger-500` left border on the title cell + danger-tone date cell. The due-date cell remains click-to-edit when overdue — just rendered in danger colors.

### 5.2 `/tasks/new` — create

Form fields: title (required), description, due date, owner. Status defaults to `todo` (the inline cell on the list/detail handles further state). Owner pre-fills to the current user — easy to clear.

Submitting creates the task and redirects to its detail page.

### 5.3 `/tasks/[id]` — detail

Shows: title (struck-through when done), status (inline cell), owner (inline cell), due date with overdue indicator, description, metadata block (created / updated / completed timestamps + actor).

Header buttons:
- "Редактирай" — links to `/tasks/[id]/edit` for title / description / due date / owner edits.
- "Изтрий" — admin only. Wired to the `deleteTask` server action via a plain form post; no two-step confirm because it's an admin-only action behind a heading already labeled with the task title.

### 5.4 `/tasks/[id]/edit` — edit

Same form shape as `/tasks/new`, pre-filled. Submitting redirects back to the detail page.

## 6. Inline-edit cells used

- **Title** — `<InlineTextCell>` from `_foundations/ui-patterns-inline-edit.md` §3.4. Required, max 200 chars; rejection rolls back. The detail-page link icon (↗) sits beside the cell so click-to-edit and click-to-open don't conflict.
- **Status** — `<InlineStatusCell>` from §3.1. Three options, color-coded.
- **Owner** — `<InlinePersonCell>` from §3.9. Active profiles only in the picker; inactive owners render with `(неактивен)` tag.
- **Due date** — `<InlineDateCell>` from §3.7. Optional; overdue indicator + top-nav badge re-evaluate on next nav via `revalidatePath`.
- **Created / Completed** — read-only with 🔒 `<ReadOnlyBadge>` (§3.12). Both are system-managed (`completedAt` auto-stamped on status → done, cleared on leaving done).

All editable cells are open team-wide (`disabled` is never set). Setting status → `done` auto-stamps `completedAt`; moving back from `done` clears it.

## 7. Audit log

Per `_foundations/audit-log.md` (pending) — every mutation logs:
- `tasks.create` — new task.
- `tasks.update` — full-form edit (title / description / due-date / owner).
- `tasks.status_changed` — inline status change.
- `tasks.owner_changed` — inline owner change.
- `tasks.field.updated` — granular per-field audit from inline-edit cells (title, dueDate). Payload carries `{ field }`; `before` + `after` carry the per-field values.
- `tasks.deleted` — admin delete.

Audit entries include `before` / `after` for diffable fields (title, description, status, owner, dueDate) and `payload` for non-diff context.

## 8. Known gaps / future work

- **Filters bar** (assignee multi-select, status multi-select within Всички). Plumbed in `lib/tasks/filters.ts` already; UI not yet built.
- **Inline description editing on the list.** Description isn't currently a column; would need either adding the column or building a detail-page inline pattern.
- **Links to other entities** when a clear use case appears.
- **Activity feed** when the foundation spec lands.

## 9. Top-nav badge

The "Задачи" link in the app header carries an accent-tone badge with the count of `me's open tasks where dueDate <= today` (i.e. due today *or* overdue). Computed once per navigation in `app/(app)/layout.tsx` alongside the existing `pendingAbsenceInbox` and `openLeadsInbox` counts. Hidden when the count is 0 — the link is just text.

The badge intentionally does not split "due today" vs "overdue" — both are actionable in the same way (open it, do it, mark done). A single number says "there are N things you should look at."
</file>

<file path="supabase/migrations/0001_auth_setup.sql">
-- Auth setup: profile sync trigger + RLS policies
-- Apply this once via Supabase Dashboard → SQL Editor → New query.
--
-- This file is the source of truth for auth-side database wiring.
-- Re-running is safe (drop-then-create everywhere it matters).

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- 1. Profile sync: when an auth.users row is created, insert a public.profiles
--    row mirroring it. Role + full_name are read from raw_user_meta_data, with
--    sensible defaults so a manual signup still produces a valid profile.
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

create or replace function public.handle_new_auth_user()
returns trigger
language plpgsql
security definer
set search_path = public
as $$
declare
  meta_role text;
  resolved_role public."Role";
begin
  meta_role := coalesce(new.raw_user_meta_data->>'role', 'user');

  if meta_role not in ('admin', 'manager', 'user') then
    resolved_role := 'user';
  else
    resolved_role := meta_role::public."Role";
  end if;

  insert into public.profiles (id, email, full_name, role, created_at, updated_at)
  values (
    new.id,
    new.email,
    coalesce(new.raw_user_meta_data->>'full_name', new.email),
    resolved_role,
    now(),
    now()
  )
  on conflict (id) do nothing;

  return new;
end;
$$;

drop trigger if exists on_auth_user_created on auth.users;
create trigger on_auth_user_created
  after insert on auth.users
  for each row execute function public.handle_new_auth_user();

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- 2. RLS policies. Service-role bypasses RLS, so admin server actions still
--    work. The policies cover what users can do with their own anon-key session.
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

alter table public.profiles               enable row level security;
alter table public.invites                enable row level security;
alter table public.audit_events           enable row level security;
alter table public.failed_login_attempts  enable row level security;

-- Helper: is the calling user an admin?
create or replace function public.is_admin()
returns boolean
language sql
stable
security definer
set search_path = public
as $$
  select exists (
    select 1 from public.profiles
    where id = auth.uid() and role = 'admin' and active = true
  );
$$;

-- Helper: is the calling user a manager or admin?
create or replace function public.is_manager_or_admin()
returns boolean
language sql
stable
security definer
set search_path = public
as $$
  select exists (
    select 1 from public.profiles
    where id = auth.uid() and role in ('admin', 'manager') and active = true
  );
$$;

-- ── profiles ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Anyone signed in can read profiles (team directory). No one writes via RLS;
-- writes go through server actions using the service-role client.
drop policy if exists profiles_select_authenticated on public.profiles;
create policy profiles_select_authenticated on public.profiles
  for select to authenticated
  using (true);

-- ── invites ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Only admins read invites; writes go through service role.
drop policy if exists invites_select_admin on public.invites;
create policy invites_select_admin on public.invites
  for select to authenticated
  using (public.is_admin());

-- ── audit_events ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Only admins read; writes go through service role.
drop policy if exists audit_events_select_admin on public.audit_events;
create policy audit_events_select_admin on public.audit_events
  for select to authenticated
  using (public.is_admin());

-- ── failed_login_attempts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Server-only table; no client reads.
-- (No SELECT policy = no rows visible to authenticated; service role bypasses.)
</file>

<file path="supabase/migrations/0002_last_admin_guard.sql">
-- Defense-in-depth: prevent the last active admin from being demoted or
-- deactivated, even by direct SQL or a misbehaving service-role caller.
-- Apply via Supabase Dashboard → SQL Editor.

create or replace function public.guard_last_admin()
returns trigger
language plpgsql
as $$
declare
  remaining_admins int;
begin
  -- Only intervene when the change would remove an admin from active duty.
  if (old.role = 'admin' and old.active = true)
     and (new.role <> 'admin' or new.active = false) then
    select count(*) into remaining_admins
    from public.profiles
    where role = 'admin'
      and active = true
      and id <> old.id;

    if remaining_admins = 0 then
      raise exception 'cannot remove last active admin'
        using errcode = 'check_violation';
    end if;
  end if;

  return new;
end;
$$;

drop trigger if exists guard_last_admin on public.profiles;
create trigger guard_last_admin
  before update on public.profiles
  for each row execute function public.guard_last_admin();
</file>

